{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 41,
  "title": "第四十一章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "上士聞道，勤而行之；"
    },
    {
      "text": "中士聞道，若存若亡；下士聞道，大笑之。不笑不足以為道。故建言有之﹕"
    },
    {
      "text": "明道若昧，"
    },
    {
      "text": "進道若退，"
    },
    {
      "text": "夷道若纇，"
    },
    {
      "text": "上德若谷，"
    },
    {
      "text": "大白若辱，"
    },
    {
      "text": "廣德若不足，"
    },
    {
      "text": "建德若偷，"
    },
    {
      "text": "質真若渝，"
    },
    {
      "text": "大方無隅，"
    },
    {
      "text": "大器晚成，"
    },
    {
      "text": "大音希聲，"
    },
    {
      "text": "大象無形，"
    },
    {
      "text": "道隱無名。夫唯道，善貸且成。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "有志也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "建，猶立也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "光而不耀。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "後其身而身先，外其身而身存。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "纇，㘨也。大夷之道，因物之性，不執平以割物，其平不見，乃更反若纇㘨也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不德其德，無所懷也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "知其白，守其黑，大白然後乃得。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "廣德不盈，廓然無形，不可滿也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "偷，匹也。建德者，因物自然，不立不施，故若偷匹。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "質真者，不矜其真，故渝。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 10,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "方而不割，故無隅也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 11,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大器成天下不持全別，故必晚成也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-13",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 12,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聽之不聞名曰希，不可得聞之音也。有聲則有分，有分則不宮而商矣，分則不能統眾，故有聲者非大音也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-14",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 13,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "有形則有分，有分者不溫則炎，不炎則寒。故象而形者，非大象。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-15",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 14,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "凡此諸善，皆是道之所成也。在象則為大象，而大象無形。在音則為大音，而大音希聲。物以之成而不見其成形，故隱而無名也。貸之非唯供其乏而已，一貸之則足以永終其德，故曰善貸也。成之不如機匠之裁，無物而不濟其形，故曰善成。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
